Depression

Gaussian

mod_dep_cont <- brm(DEP ~ 1 + DEM_01 + Exp_Group + Language + year + year:Exp_Group + (1|id+schoolnum),  
               data = cov_5, 
               family = gaussian,
               warmup = 1000, iter = 4000, 
               cores = 4, chains = 4, 
               seed = 123)

Results

Summary

  • Although Rhat and Bulk_ESS look good, the density plot looks terrible. We shouldnt use this model at all for our results.

Gamma

mod_dep_gamma <- brm(DEP ~ 1 + DEM_01 + Exp_Group + Language + year + year:Exp_Group + (1|id+schoolnum),  
               data = cov_5, 
               family = hurdle_gamma(link = "log"),
               warmup = 1000, iter = 4000, 
               cores = 4, chains = 4, 
               seed = 123)

Results

Summary

  • Small, non-significant, negative effect (slower growth in depression in intervention group compared to control group)
  • Model diagnostics look good (Rhat below 1.01 and Bulk-ESS above 1000), density plot looks good, trace plots I think look ok
